    <div class="highlight-box warn">
      <strong>Why does TypeScript not catch the StackItem bug?</strong>
      <p style="color:var(--text-muted)">Because the <code>component</code> prop is typed as <code>React.ReactNode</code> (not <code>React.ElementType</code>). This is a permissive type that accepts strings, JSX elements, and other React nodes. TypeScript sees no error, but React crashes at runtime when it tries to use a ReactNode as a constructor. This is a known PF type definition weakness.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
